Biggest lesson in my twenties so far:

Remain calm & still. Stay within your group where safety lies. Explore soft bed sheets, matcha cups in the early morning, rely on books instead of your screen, and most importantly treat your body as you would for that career, reputation, and respect from others.

Keep those shoulders relaxed and disregard any tense bodies roaming around trying to distract you from your own self. Find yourself!! You know what you like, so do them. Bring your ideal lifestyle in motion! Take that Pilates class, do your daily green cleanse, meditate, educate, be educated, keep an open mind…just do your thing🫧

-mel 🎀

🩷What people don’t tell you is:

Healing is needed in all aspects of life - relationships, friendships, self discovery.

Pay attention to what agrees with your body whether it be foods, social settings, clothes you wear, or even the words you say to yourself. Be mindful of your thoughts, be aware of your actions, be in tune with your body. 

In result, not only did i start creating my dream life, but i look even better than i was before. 

🌟 it takes time & patience. You will see ✨it✨in a few years☁️💞
